				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\eta }_{sol-pow}=W/({I}_{p} \times {A}_{s})=W/{Q}_{s}$$\end{document}

On a clear day noon, a high-performance solar panel yields a maximum efficiency of 15%. The refrigeration machine efficiency is determined as the ratio of cooling power (Qe) to the work input (W).4ηpow-cool=Qe/W\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
